EPISTEMIC HONESTY NOTICE

AION-BRAIN maintains honest convergence states across all frameworks.
Users of this work should know:

    FSVE v3.5    — M-STRONG (30 FCL entries, EV 0.813)
    LAV v1.5     — M-STRONG (45 FCL entries, 77.5% running mean)
    AION v3.0    — M-NASCENT (specified, validation in progress)
    ASL v2.0     — M-NASCENT (specified, validation in progress)
    GENESIS v1.0 — M-NASCENT (specified, validation in progress)
    CDIP v1.5    — M-NASCENT (CEV v1.0 audit complete, FCL pending)
    EID v0.1     — M-NASCENT (specified February 2026, pre-validation)

No framework is represented as more validated than it is.
Certainty engineering means knowing exactly where confidence is
justified and where it is not.

